After back-to-back boundaries, Elgar calmly defends this one.

FOUR! First boundary off the cover drive in this innings. Fuller around off, Elgar gets on his front foot and creams it through cover. Cover drives are always beautiful but when a southpaw hits it they look even better.
FOUR! Good shot! Fuller around off, Elgar strokes it through point for a boundary.

Shami comes and straightaway there is excitment. He starts with a bouncer. It is around off, Elgar looks to pull but then decides to pull away from the shot. He ends up lobbing up off the upper half of his bat. Luckily for Elgar it falls in no man's land on the on side.
Mohammed Shami to bowl now.
On the fourth stump line, Faf lets it be.
On the pads again, Elgar glances it through fine leg to change ends.
Too wide to make the batter play this time. Elgar shoulders arms.
Good length ball angled in to the batter, Dean stands tall to keep it out.
Length on middle, Faf this time tucks it behind square for a single.
Misses his length on the first ball of the new over, does Umesh. Strays the ball on the leg side. Faf goes for a flick but misses.
Fuller around off, Elgar blocks it.
Length ball on off, Elgar works it to square leg and shouts a loud no.
Another one on the pads, Elgar does not time his flick well this time. Ashwin runs to his right from square leg and keeps it to a dot with a dive.
Outside off, Elgar leaves it alone.
FOUR! Poor ball from Ishant. He strays down on the pads. These are easy pickings for Elgar. He just eases his flick through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Around off, Dean defends it towards backward point.
Outside off, Faf leaves it alone.
Fuller on middle, Elgar pushes it wide of mid on for a single.
Length delivery around off, Elgar defends it off his back foot towards point.
Fuller on off, Elgar pushes it wide of point. Jadeja, who is lightning quick gets to the ball quickly showing his athleticism.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Well played. Slightly fuller delivery outside off, Elgar plays it nicely through point. Mayank gives it a chase and saves it with a dive before the ropes. Two taken.
Fuller on off, du Plessis keeps it out.
Another gem of a delivery. Fuller around off and middle, du Plessis looks to defend but it jags back in and takes the inside edge of the bat and goes behind square on the leg side.
On the pads, Faf looks to flick but it goes off the inner half of his bat through square leg for a couple. Du Plessis is off the mark but not in the most convincing manner. The trail now is 300.
Good ball and a good  leave. Outside off and it comes in off the deck. Faf shows awareness of his off pole and offers a very good leave.
Length ball around off, Elgar punches it towards point and gets to the other end.
In the air but safe again. Elgar continues to ride his luck. Short ball closer to the body, Elgar looks to pull but it goes off the upper half of his bat wide of mid-wicket for a single.
Good length ball outside off, du Plessis leaves it alone.
Another one down the leg side, Faf though does not get any bat on it as he misses his flick.
No Bavuma. It's skipper Faf du Plessis who has finally come out at number 4. Interesting!

OUT! Caught! Brilliant catch from Wridhimann Saha  and smart bowling from Umesh. He was bowling in and around off and then he surprises Theunis with a one down the leg side. He tried it in the last over but that was way down, this one is closer to the body. De Bruyn looks to flick but the ball kisses his bat and goes to the left of the keeper. Saha dives to that side and takes a one-handed stunner. If you were wondering why Saha was picked over Pant, then this catch is the reason. He is hailed as one of the best keepers in the world and this is a proof of it. South Africa in all sorts of trouble. 2 down in the 6th over of the day.
Good length ball on off, Theunis pushes it to point.
Fuller and closer to off, de Bruyn defends it off the front foot.
Umesh continues to bowl outside off to Theunis. De Bruyn leaves it alone.
Around off, Elgar this time calmly defends it.

EDGED AND FOUR! Another boundary off the edge. Fuller around off, it zips away after pitching. Elgar goes for it in a wild way and the ball takes a fat outside edge of his willow and goes uppishly wide of gully for a boundary.

Another edge that does not carry. If you're thinking the slip should come in then that will be difficult as there is good carry. Length ball on off, Elgar looks to defend with soft hands but gets a thick outside edge. The fact that he played it with soft hands worked in his favour as that was the reason the ball did not carry to Kohli at third slip.
On off, Elgar keeps it out.

EDGED AND FOUR! Third boundary of the innings and all three have come off the outside edge. Slightly fuller around off, Elgar looks to defend it with soft hands but the ball takes the outside edge. The ball goes right between gully and third slip and the ball goes away to the fence. Rahane dives but cannot get his hand to it as the ball was well wide.
Good length ball outside off, Elgar calmly leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, de Bruyn defends it to get through a good over of Umesh.

FOUR BYES! Poor ball from Umesh. He misses his line and bowls one down the leg side. Theunis looks to flick but misses. The ball keeps on going with the angle as even Saha, who was diving to his left cannot save it. The idea was right to surprise him with a ball on middle and leg after going in and around off but the execution was not.
Goes fuller around off, Theunis defends it towards point.
On the fourth stump line, de Bruyn does not disturb that.
Good length delivery outside off, Theunis leaves it alone.

Nice swing and carry on this one. Good length ball just around off, it moves away off the surface. Theunis shoulders arms to it. The ball goes to Saha at chest height. Seldom you see such carry for pacers in India.
Fuller on off, Elgar defends it to get through the over.
Goes wide of the off stump again, does Ishant. Dean Elgar shoulders arms to it.
Ishant comes closer to the off pole, Elgar defends it off the front foot.
Ishant continues to bowl outside off to Elgar. He once again calmly leaves it.
Good length ball outside off, Elgar does not go chasing after it.
Comes around the wicket and bowls it on a length outside off, Dean leaves it alone. Late swing for Ishant.
FOUR! Streaky! Fuller around off, de Bruyn looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes wide of the diving Rahane at gully for a boundary.
Once again Theunis does not go chasing after the ball away from the stump.
Length delivery outside off, Theunis leaves it alone.

EDGED AND FOUR! Length delivery around off, Theunis looks to defend it with soft hands but it goes off the outside edge. It falls short of Virat Kohli at third slip and goes through him for a boundary.

Could have been disastrous for South Africa. Back of a length ball on off, Elgar defends it with soft hands towards cover-point and calls for a quick single. Theunis responds but he knows it is a suicidal run. Mayank Agarwal gets to the ball quickly and has a shy at the striker's end but misses. A direct hit and Theunis would've been walking into the pavilion.
Umesh starts with a length delivery on off, Elgar starts his innings with a back foot defense.
Umesh Yadav to share the new ball with Ishant Sharma from the other end. He had struck in the first over of the first innings. Can he do the same this innings?
Fuller on off, Theunis defends it to get through the over. Wicket maiden for Ishant to start the innings.
Another one outside off, Theunis shoulders arms to it.
On the fourth stump line, Theunis lets it carry to the keeper.
Ohh! Full and this one comes back in sharply too. De Bruyn does well to defend it off the front foot.
Theunis de Bruyn walks out at number 3.

OUT! LBW! India start with a bang! The first one was on a length and came back in. Markram was lucky to survive that but on this occasion he is not. Ishant goes slightly fuller and once again gets the ball in to the right-hander. Markram looks to defend but the ball hits him on high on the pads. The Indian players go up in a huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Markram has a word with his partner, Elgar. Dean does not look sure and just when Markram was about to review the timer gets to zero. Markram's first pair in Tests. Ishant gets his first wicket of the game. Well hold on, Ball Tracker later on rolls in and it is a disappointing news for Markram, Elgar and the whole of South Africa. The Ball Tracker shows the ball was going onto miss the stumps.

Excellent delivery to start the innings. Ishant starts with a good length ball outside off, it comes back in viciously. Markram offers a dangerous leave but as they say, if you leave and it does not hit you then it is a good leave.
